#: ../../source/config/configuration.rst:11
msgid "Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/config/configuration.rst:13
msgid "Once Picard has been installed on your system, the next step is to configure it to your preferences.  The configuration consists of enabling the desired screen sections for display, selecting the desired actions, and setting the various options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/config/configuration.rst:19
msgid "Screen Setup"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/config/configuration.rst:21
msgid "The screen setup is found under the :menuselection:`\"View\"` item on the menu bar.  To enable the display of an item, simply check the box for the screen option.  The items are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/config/configuration.rst:24
msgid "**File Browser**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/config/configuration.rst:26
msgid "This displays a file browser on the left side of the screen for selecting files and directories for processing.  Files and directories can also be selected using your system's file browser by dragging and dropping them onto the Picard application."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/config/configuration.rst:30
msgid "**Cover Art**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/config/configuration.rst:32
msgid "This displays the cover art for the currently selected item (track or release) in a window to the right of the tags section of the display.  This allows you to select or replace the cover art saved with the release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/config/configuration.rst:36
msgid "**Actions**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/config/configuration.rst:38
msgid "This displays the button bar of the actions performed by Picard, located just below the menu bar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/config/configuration.rst:40
msgid "**Search**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/config/configuration.rst:42
msgid "This displays the manual search box to the right of the \"Actions\" button bar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/config/configuration.rst:44
msgid "**Player**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/config/configuration.rst:46
msgid "This displays the built-in player for playing selected audio files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/config/configuration.rst:50
msgid "Action Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/config/configuration.rst:52
msgid "The action options are found under the :menuselection:`\"Options\"` item on the menu bar.  There are three available actions that Picard can perform when saving selected music files:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/config/configuration.rst:55
msgid "**Rename Files**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/config/configuration.rst:57
msgid "Picard will rename each file in accordance with the naming script."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/config/configuration.rst:59
msgid "**Move Files**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/config/configuration.rst:61
msgid "Picard will move files to the target directory in accordance with the naming script."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/config/configuration.rst:63
msgid "**Save Tags**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/config/configuration.rst:65
msgid "Picard will update the metadata tags in the files in accordance with the specified option settings and tagging scripts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/config/configuration.rst:70
msgid "Option Settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/config/configuration.rst:72
msgid "The option settings are found under the :menuselection:`\"Options --> Options...\"` item on the menu bar.  This will open a new window with the option groups listed in a tree format on the left hand side, and the individual settings on the right hand side.  This is where the majority of Picard's customization is performed."
msgstr ""
